  "standardBio": "Stonegrub, titled among keepers as “Bedrock Companion,” carries quiet loyalty in every movement. Native to Stoneheart Canyon, the species endures through dust and canyon grit, leaving traces that other Riftlings can follow like soft maps. Wild groups form loose bonds rather than rigid packs; a sleepy individual may become the emotional center of a small hearthline. They eat Stonefruit eagerly and dislike food that smells of neglect or spoilage. Ancient keepers carved Stonegrub silhouettes into travel stones, believing the species guided the lost. Modern hatcheries record them as reliable companions; their practical problem-solving intelligence makes training feel like conversation. Their signature ability, Stonegrub's Hearth Slam, reflects a life shaped by Stoneheart Canyon more than by arena ambition. Some believe rarity equals destiny. Stonegrub stories are meaningful without being prophetic. Young Stonegrubs practice Stonegrub's Hearth Slam as play long before they understand battle. Adults teach by demonstration: where to rest, what to avoid, how to share warmth or shade.",
  "fullLore": "Stonegrubs first condensed from residual fossilhum along the living edges of Stoneheart Canyon after early Rift fractures cooled into weather. Their eggs appear where dust and canyon grit gathers into stillness—never in the loudest danger, always in the pocket of calm beside it. Early surveyors mistook them for ambient phenomena until a Stonegrub returned a dropped lantern, carefully, as if returning a promise.\n\nIn ancient eras, regional peoples treated Stonegrubs as omen-bearers rather than pets. Carvings show them walking ahead of caravans, pausing at unstable ground, and curling around children during ashfall or fog. The species was never “tamed” in the old sense; it chose. That choice culture survives in modern Riftkeeper etiquette: you do not yank a Stonegrub into a bond. You invite, wait, and keep the invitation honest.\n\nModern history is quieter and more practical. Hatcheries map Stonegrub care cycles with the same seriousness given to rare lines, because common does not mean shallow. Stoneheart Canyon still holds wild populations that trade soft greetings with passerby pets. After major Rift events, Stonegrubs often appear first at recovery centers—not as heroes, but as inventory clerks of comfort, counting who is cold, hungry, or afraid.\n\nNatural behavior is sleepy at the core and adaptable at the edges. They are light-framed with precise limbs, companion-sized, easy to cradle, and communicate through tap-codes on stone or wood. Socially, they prefer small trusted circles; strangers are assessed by scent, posture, and whether a keeper’s voice stays kind under stress. Intelligence presents as practical problem-solving intelligence. They sleep in shallow scrapes and prefer weather that matches their affinity’s comfort band.\n\nEcologically, Stonegrubs act as seed dispersers of calm within Stoneheart Canyon. Allies often include Pebblit and Crystowl; rivalries with Quartzhorn and Mossprig are usually about nesting space or shiny refuse, not blood feuds. Predators are rare—most threats come from collapsing terrain and careless machines rather than jaws.\n\nCulture around them is affectionate and slightly superstitious. An old keeper journal swears a Stonegrub refused to leave an injured stranger until dawn warmth returned. Collectors prize unusual cosmetics, yet marketplace notes remind buyers that verified care history matters more than glitter. The common misunderstanding remains: Some believe rarity equals destiny. Stonegrub stories are meaningful without being prophetic. The hidden truth keepers debate in soft rooms is simpler and stranger: When deeply bonded, a Stonegrub shares short dream-images of places it has never physically visited.\n\nFrom egg to evolved form, their life story stays continuous. Eggs look like copper seed-cases veined with stone light. Hatchlings are clumsy with sincerity; adults become specialists of place; evolved stages sharpen instinct without erasing childhood habits. Battle tendencies favor protective bursts, and evolution philosophy insists transformation should answer lived experience—not fashion.\n\nFor Riftkeepers, a Stonegrub is a living chapter of Stoneheart Canyon. Feed it Stonefruit, respect its sleepy tempo, and it will teach you the region’s quieter grammar: which winds lie, which stones remember, which silences are safe. Personal quests often begin with a shell symbol, a remembered scent, or a dream of a door that only opens when the bond is honest. That is the Stonegrub bargain—not destiny sold at rarity price, but a life that continues because you showed up.",
